default issues paper, 
defaultDisability, Poverty and Development
default (2000). We therefore recommend
default that DFID finances specifically targeted disability programmes as well as enabling disabled people and their families to access mainstream public services and development initiatives (including water and sanitation, public health, education and social pro
defaulttection).
