default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIt has long been recognised, especially in rural development and international gender studies, that the most sustainable and efficient 
defaultoutcomes of development initiatives occur when participatory approaches to policy and programme design are employed
default. Within the international disability and development sector, a good example of this was the negotiation process of the UNCRPD. 
default&#xa0;
default3.21
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultA
defaultdopting a
default participatory approach, if undertaking in a non-tokenistic manner, will incur financial
default 
defaultand human costs
default – for example provision of sign language interpreters,
default physically accessible venues
default, covering transport etc. We recommend 
defaultthat explicit reference is 
defaultmade
default 
defaultwithin the DFID disability strategy to the need
default to involve
default disabled people and their allies in the development of DFID-funded disability initiatives. It will also be important to explicitly state what processes and methodology will be employed to ensu
defaultre such engagement.
default&#xa0;
default3.22
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe believe
default that both disabled and non-disabled people have a legitimate role to play in relation to policy design, programme implementation and evaluation. 
