defaultexclusion of disability in international development are substantial. In 2000, the World Bank estimated that the annual loss to global GDP of people with disabilities not working who were in a position to 
defaultdo so
default was between $1
default.37 trillion and $1,94 trillion
default. This figure is
default likely
default to have increased substantially since 2000.
